parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system leaks and fires can cause serious injury or death, as well as damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.
symptoms: fire or flames under the vehicle or in the engine compartment
fuel spraying from the fuel lines or distributor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents. In severe cases, it can also lead to engine fires, which can result in total vehicle loss and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: burning smell or smoke from under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of issues, including engine stalling, fires, and damage to critical components. This can lead to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: burning smell or smoke from under the hood

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the engine due to overheating can cause a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents. This can also lead to damage to critical engine components and potentially result in costly repairs.
symptoms: Engine stalls at high speeds (30-40 mph) after the engine gets hot
dealer unable to find a problem in any system.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Acceleration due to Throttle Body Linkage Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body linkage can cause the vehicle to accelerate suddenly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially fatal consequences.
symptoms: The vehicle surges out of control
the vehicle takes off immediately after shifting into drive

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the seatbelt anchor from the floor of the vehicle can cause the seatbelt to malfunction, leading to increased risk of injury or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt anchor detaches from the floor
the seatbelt buckle comes unattached while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seatbelt to malfunction, leading to increased risk of injury or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt buckle fails to latch securely
the seatbelt buckle opens with slight movement or tug
the seatbelt buckle does not latch or sometimes lets loose when buckled.
